programme.title: The FBI Files: Radical Agenda
programme.desc: In the 1970's a string of bank robberies and bombings spread fear and destruction along the east coast. The FBI faced a new breed of criminal, the domestic terrorist.

programme.title: The FBI Files: Deadly Takeover
programme.desc: Two armed bank robbers hit a Seattle bank taking over 150,000 dollars. Before they can escape police confront them and the pair splits up. As authorities search block by block they learn one was a career criminal with a long history of violence.

programme.title: The FBI Files: Cracking The Cartel
programme.desc: A mother and child are kidnapped, a bystander is murdered. Violence such as this shattered a quiet Texas neighborhood and exposed a drug cartel that flourished where it was least expected.

programme.title: The FBI Files: Dead Run
programme.desc: In Pennsylvania, an inmate escaped with the help of his female accomplice. Following a trail of fraudulent credit card receipts and deaths, authorities track the pair, but always find themselves one step behind.(n)

programme.title: The FBI Files: Temple of Fear
programme.desc: In Miami, the discovery of a mutilated body sent investigators on the trail of a deadly cult. But agents found a wall of silence around the cult's members. Potential witnesses, terrified of reprisals, refused to talk.(n)

programme.title: The FBI Files: Terror In Disguise
programme.desc: Banks use a variety of devices to discourage would-be robbers: security cameras, silent alarms, and exploding dye packs. But when an elusive bank robber targeted Seattle's banks, none of these precautions were effective.(n)

programme.title: The FBI Files: A Model Killer
programme.desc: It's a model's job to rivet the public's attention. But in 1984, some aspiring models began attracting publicity in a terrible new way.(n)

programme.title: The FBI Files: Deadly Threat
programme.desc: A suspected drug dealer would stop at nothing to keep local and federal authorities from building a case against him. When his organization started targeting the government itself, federal agencies went on high alert.(n)

programme.title: The FBI Files: Evil Intent
programme.desc: Drops of blood and a torn screen were all that's left to tell authorities what happened to a woman in Indiana. The 21 yr. old victim was taken from her home on a spring morning. She appeared to have no real enemies, there was no clear motive.(n)

programme.title: The FBI Files: Deadly Paradise
programme.desc: It should have been Shangri-La, but when bad blood developed, piracy took over and the only law was the law of the jungle.(n)

programme.title: The FBI Files: Hunter's Game
programme.desc: In the 1970's and 80s, people went to Alaska looking for a fresh start, to reinvent themselves, or to disappear for a while. Some of those disappearances weren't by choice.(n)

programme.title: The FBI Files: The Predator
programme.desc: In the early 1990's, Washington, D.C., became the murder capital of the nation. Few were left untouched by gang violence, which was ignited by the drug trade. By 1994, that violence would strike at the very heart of law enforcement.(n)

programme.title: The FBI Files: Held For Ransom
programme.desc: Wealth has its rewards, but it also brings its dangers. Kidnapping is one of them. No ordeal is more horrifying for a family than to have a child taken.(n)

programme.title: The FBI Files: Deadly Stranger
programme.desc: The body of a young woman found burned in a truck launched a manhunt to find her killer. When more bodies began to turn up across the country, the FBI believed the cases were linked. Investigators had a suspect. They just couldn't find him.(n)

programme.title: Fear Factor: A Traverse The Dam, Bee Headed, Water Coffin
programme.desc: The Big Tujunga Dam towers hundreds of feet high. Contestant's head and shoulders will be covered in bees. The contestants will lie in a small Plexiglas coffin which has holes drilled in the bottom and on the sides.

programme.title: Fear Factor: A Stage Coach Net Drag, Cod Stew, Pipe To Pipe To Pipe Walk
programme.desc: A cargo net is draped off the back of a stage coach. Contestants take turns playing street hockey goalie as a hockey puck machine shoots pucks at them. Three wet pipes are suspended by cranes 90 feet up in the air.

programme.title: Fear Factor: A Speed Boat To Helicopter Ladder, Worm Transfer, Car Through Building
programme.desc: Contestants must exit from a speed boat by grabbing onto a ladder that is hanging out of a helicopter. A contestant has to transfer mealworms from a Plexiglas container to a scale. Contestants must launch themselves in a car off a 3 foot high ramp.

programme.title: Fear Factor: A Burning Building, Scorpian Pit, Rotating Climbing Wall
programme.desc: Contestants will climb up 4 stories on a hook and ladder with 70 pounds of gear. A contestant must lay in a pit for 2 minutes while scorpions are dropped on them. Contestants will be put on a platform suspended from a crane 100 feet in the air.(n)

programme.title: Fear Factor: Helicopter Body Drop, Slug Bugs and Bile, Build-A-Bridge
programme.desc: Contestants fall out of a speeding helicopter. Contestant must consume 10 live slugs and a shot of cow bile. Each contestant must cross between two buildings by placing three planks in front of them on top of two tight ropes as they walk.(n)

programme.title: Fear Factor: A Junk Yard Dog, Confidence Chamber, Car Carrier Drive-Thru
programme.desc: Contestants must find their way through an urban assault building. Contestants will also have to drive their cars onto the back of a car carrier as they both drive down a closed highway.(n)

programme.title: Fear Factor: Drowning Closet, Ostrich Eggs, Merry Go Round
programme.desc: Contestant is placed in an empty plexi container ten feet high. Contestant must eat an entire, 3 pound raw ostrich egg. The contestant will stand in the center of a rotating circle of truss, which is suspended from a crane 100 feet in the air.(n)

programme.title: Fear Factor: Scooter Plank, Deer Jewels, 100 Year Old Egg Nog, Trapped Under The Ice
programme.desc: Contestants pick wrapped gifts to determine the amount of reindeer testicles they will eat and ride a motorized scooter from one platform to another platform in this special Christmas episode. Joe Rogan hosts.(n)

programme.title: Fear Factor: A Inverted Heli Hang, Horse Rectum, Sky Walker
programme.desc: Contestant are hung upside down by their ankles hovering over the water. Contestants are presented cooked horse rectums to eat. The contestant will be placed high in the air on a giant 40 foot square truss structure.(n)

programme.title: Fear Factor: Barrel Rolling,Rat Transfer,Car Jump Into Pond
programme.desc: Contestants must stand on top of a large cylinder. Contestants round up dead feeder rats using only their mouths and throw them into a bucket. A contestant will be strapped into a modified car.(n)

programme.title: Fear Factor: Spin Cycle, Breakfast of Champions, Stilt Walking
programme.desc: Contestant will be placed on a 20 foot rope ladder. Contestants play a game to determine quantity of food they will have to eat. Contestant must walk across a 12 inch wide and 60 foot long beam suspended 100 feet in the air.(n)

programme.title: Fear Factor: A Ferris Wheel, Fear Factor Pizza, Water Platform
programme.desc: Contestants play a game tossing pizza pans into big pots to determine which horrifying toppings will be on their pizza, then balance on a spinning wheel in this episode.(n)

programme.title: Fear Factor: Bobbing In Blood,Tomato Hornworm,Skunk Crawl
programme.desc: Contestant bobs in tank of cow blood trying to retrieve as many dive rings. Contestants throw darts to determine the number of hornworms that they will eat. The contestant crawls through dark tunnels and retrieves 3 dead skunks.(n)

programme.title: Fear Factor: Vertical Two Square, Eel Tan, Heli Rodeo
programme.desc: In one stunt, the contestant will be placed on a 30 foot truss structure. Contestant moves electric eels from one side of tank to the other. In another stunt, the contestant will be seated on a barrel hung by 20 foot long cables underneath a helicopter.(n)

programme.title: Fear Factor: Save Your Spouse, Roach Transfer, Couples Hang
programme.desc: Contestants will be placed in a Plexiglas cabinet. One person retrieves roaches using only their mouth and transfers it to their partner's mouth, who in turn drops it into another bin.(n)

programme.title: Ice Pilots: Push Comes to Shove
programme.desc: Trying to make his mark at Buffalo, Duane lands two more Electra contracts. But his over- zealous efforts result in a clash with the crew and with Joe, and a down-to-the-wire midnight departure to meet a deadline.

programme.title: Ice Pilots: The Doghouse
programme.desc: Duane's decision to leave the Electra crew unsupervised while he spends time at home jeopardizes the completion of a major contract. Young DC-3 co-pilot Graeme sees his chance to move up to a bigger plane disappear when he falls out of favour with Joe.

programme.title: Ice Pilots: Ice Strip
programme.desc: Mechanic Jimmy is sent to a northern mining camp to create an ice landing strip on a remote lake where AJ will have to land a DC-3 and the much bigger C-46. New co-pilot Tyler faces the ultimate test - flying the sked with Joe.

programme.title: Ice Pilots: Expect the Unexpected
programme.desc: Engine troubles on the C-46 during the valley run force Devan to shut down an engine. High winds wreak havoc for Devan and his crew on another C-46 mission to help clean up an oil spill in the Northwest Territories.

programme.title: Ice Pilots: Coming Home
programme.desc: Rookie waterbomber pilot Scott gets his first taste of action when Buffalo responds to an emergency callout to fight fires in Alberta. Mikey and Rod think they hit the jackpot when they buy a million dollar firefighting plane on eBay at a bargain price.(n)

programme.title: Ice Pilots: Dark Skies
programme.desc: When Yellowknife and the northern aviation community are rocked by three crashes within a month, Joe places an extra emphasis on safety, which is why he only trusts himself to perform a dangerous-looking DC-3 stunt landing for a visiting film crew.(n)

programme.title: Ice Pilots: Shut Down
programme.desc: Joe receives a negative visit from Transport Canada when inspectors threaten to shut down the airline. Ray and the Electra crew fly to Sachs Harbour to pick up a unique load - the hides, wool, and meat of 250 musk oxen.(n)

programme.title: Ice Pilots: A Tale of Two Pilots
programme.desc: Weighed down by the responsibility of training a new rampie, and struggling to get out of Joe's doghouse, DC-3 co-pilot Tyler gets a once in a lifetime opportunity to stunt fly in his Cessna 150 for a visiting film crew.(n)

programme.title: Ice Pilots: Ice Jam
programme.desc: After taking command of an intense airlift, and dealing with the ugliest Electra load he's ever seen, Scott takes a scary fall on the icy tarmac. City girl Christine moves to Yellowknife to give the unglamorous rampie life a shot.(n)

programme.title: Ice Pilots: A Very Buffalo Christmas
programme.desc: A week before Christmas, Buffalo agrees to lend a hand to an RCMP initiative to fly toys to isolated communities in the north. But a series of problems with the Electra leave the company in a jam.(n)

programme.title: Ice Pilots: Crash Landing
programme.desc: Captain Ray Weber leads his crew on a multi-trip mission that requires landing on a rough ice strip on a remote lake. The ice strip landing goes fine, but when the plane takes off from the strip, the right landing gear gets stuck in the wheel well.(n)

programme.title: Ice Pilots: For Sale By Owner
programme.desc: When South Korean buyers come to Buffalo to look at a water bomber, the pressure is on mechanic Cory to get the plane ready. But a landing gear emergency puts him and chief pilot Justin in serious danger.(n)

programme.title: Ice Pilots: Over Seas
programme.desc: Buffalo has to get a CL-215 water bomber to buyers in Korea. So Justin and Cory fly the plane to Vancouver Harbour, where it will be hoisted onto a cargo ship sailing across the Pacific Ocean to its destinatin, a method of delivery no one has ever tried.(n)

programme.title: Ice Pilots: Water Wings
programme.desc: In South Korea, Cory and Justin meet the ship delivering Buffalo's water bomber plane to buyers there but are frustrated by the buyers' poor planning. Tempers flare when they try to get the plane off the ship and delivered to its final destination.(n)

programme.title: Ice Pilots: Meltdown
programme.desc: As spring arrives and Ray's retirement day approaches, Sean surprises everyone by leaving Buffalo for a job with the competition. So Buffalo brings in Electra pilot Brian Harrison to finish the contract.(n)

programme.title: Ice Pilots: North Atlantic Convoy
programme.desc: Greenland's Narsarsuaq airport - known as one the world's most dangerous approaches - looms on the horizon as Cory and Justin begin a trans-global journey to deliver two CL-215 water bombers to Turkey. Christine pushes to become a DC-3 co-pilot,.(n)

programme.title: Inazuma Eleven Go: Explosion Ultimate Thunder!
programme.desc: Raimon attempts a comeback using their super tactic, but end up surrendering a goal to Royal Academy instead. Raimon's offense is powerless in the face of Royal Academy's overwhelming special moves.

programme.title: Inazuma Eleven Go: A Revolutionary Wind!
programme.desc: The day after their blistering battle in the regional semifinals, the Raimon players are ordered to meet at Royal Academy. There, they learn the stunning truth behind their match with the academy.

programme.title: Inazuma Eleven Go: Ravaging Fangs of the Sea Kings!
programme.desc: Determined to free Football from the clutches of Fifth Sector, the Raimon Eleven prepare to revolt. With the regional championship against Pirates Cove Merchant Marine Academy Academy coming up, morale is high, and losing is not an option.

programme.title: Inazuma Eleven Go: Fly Arion’s Fighting Spirit
programme.desc: The true revolution won't occur until the crowds watching are reminded of the power of real Football and decide to take a stand. The Raimon Eleven welcome back members who had quit, and the regional championship match begins.

programme.title: Inazuma Eleven Go: The Autumn Sky Challengers!
programme.desc: The Holy Road tournament is finally underway. Surrounded by powerful enemies sent by Fifth Sector, the matches ahead will be the toughest yet. So the team practices harder than ever, reminding themselves that no opponent is unbeatable.

programme.title: Inazuma Eleven Go: Gather, At The Flag Of Revolution
programme.desc: After seeing the newcomer's strange behavior in a practice match with the residents of ''Windsor Manor' flats, Bagriel Garcia (Gabi) begins to suspect the boy may be a Seed agent sent by Fifth Sector.

programme.title: Inazuma Eleven Go: The Fearsome Cyclone Arena
programme.desc: The first round of the Holy Road tournament gets underway at Aerodrome Arena. The Raimon Eleven are put on the defensive by Lunar Sea (Military) Academy's formations and attacks, which take full advantage of special contraptions unique to the venue.(n)

programme.title: Inazuma Eleven Go: Revive Our Football!
programme.desc: Raimon uses Aitor and Gabi's stellar tandem skills to combat Lunar Sea's tactical play. When Arion uses his Fighting Spirit to even the score, momentum shifts to Raimon.(n)

programme.title: Inazuma Eleven Go: He’s back!
programme.desc: Following in Aitor's footsteps, a new player tries out for Raimon. Coaches Evans and Sharp see his love for the game and readily accept him, and despite having only two months experience, he quickly integrates himself with the team.(n)

programme.title: Inazuma Eleven Go: The Adversarial White Devil
programme.desc: Alpine has fallen under the control of Fifth Sector, and Raimon is tasked with rescuing them. Knowing that Alpine's stout defence can stand up against Thunderbolt, Raimon prepares a surprising new tactical play.(n)

programme.title: Inazuma Eleven Go: Fierce Fight on the Ice vs Alpine Jr High!
programme.desc: Alpine striker Njord Snio's special shot gives the team an early lead. While Raimon has mastered using spikes to run across the icy pitch, their new tactical play is powerless against Alpine's masterful skills.(n)

programme.title: Inazuma Eleven Go: Coach Sharp’s Apprehension!
programme.desc: After their ferocious match against Alpine, Coach Evans makes an announcement that rocks Arion and the rest of Raimon. Soon thereafter, the team starts a new training regimen that prevents them from touching the ball.(n)

programme.title: Inazuma Eleven Go: Challenge Against Kirkwood!
programme.desc: Raimon finds their core skills improving thanks to their coach's new training scheme. But while the team is committed to making their revolution happen, Arion and J.P. face trouble with a new special move.(n)

programme.title: Inazuma Eleven Go: Tactical confrontation! Love vs Sharp!
programme.desc: As the match begins, the stadium's unique gimmick proves an unexpected obstacle for both teams. The Kirkwood side, however, is united under their coach's words: "If we beat Raimon, we can see the road ahead.".(n)

programme.title: Inazuma Eleven Go: The Arrival of Brave Samurai Musashi
programme.desc: As the second half begins, Roma manages to even the score. And while Raimon starts to find its flow, Langford Ash's selfish play threatens to rip Kirkwood apart.(n)

programme.title: Inazuma Eleven Go: Miracle of the Revolutionary Wind
programme.desc: After a pitched battle against Kirkwood, Arion and the rest of Raimon train for their next match. The team undergoes a trial-and-error process with J.P., who is attempting to gain a Fighting Spirit in order to better contribute.(n)

programme.title: Inazuma Eleven Go: A Mysterious Enemy. Mirage Middle School.
programme.desc: Raimon's quarterfinal opponent in Holy Road is Mirage Middle School, but while the team trains for the match, Wan-Chang's heart isn't in it. He's troubled both by his previous lineup demotion and Mirage striker Harrold Houdini.(n)

programme.title: Inazuma Eleven Go: Impossible to Defend. Phantom Shot
programme.desc: The Mirage challenge begins with Wan-Chang in the starting line-up, and he sees the match as a chance to tell Harrold how he feels. Luke, meanwhile, is unable to give Wan-Chang the news he learned from the mysterious girl.(n)

programme.title: Inazuma Eleven Go: Shocking Baton Pass. Keeper Change.
programme.desc: Coach Sharp realizes how to take advantage of the stadium, and his new tactics give Raimon a quick second-half equalizer. Meanwhile, Wan-Chang finally learns the truth of his past from a primary-school friend.(n)

programme.title: Inazuma Eleven Go: Reunion of Fate
programme.desc: Raimon has finally advanced to the Holy Road semi-finals. Their next opponent, Universal Middle School, is said to have "perfect players" gifted in all aspects of football.(n)

programme.title: Inazuma Eleven Go: Glasswork Genius
programme.desc: Arion sets aside his anxiety, rekindles his passion for football, and devotes himself to practice once more. Meanwhile, Sam invites J.P. to try goalkeeping after seeing his performance on the pitch.(n)

programme.title: Inazuma Eleven Go: Sun Spirit Unleashed
programme.desc: The day of the Holy Road semi-final is here! Raimon, confident in their quest to restore "real" football, takes on the "perfect" Universal Middle School. But Arion sees a familiar face on the opposing sideline.(n)

programme.title: Inazuma Eleven Go: Arion versus Sol
programme.desc: Victor has shocking words for Arion: "You're the only one on Raimon who isn't playing seriously right now." Arion wonders if it's because of his concern for Sol Daystar, whose illness makes him too weak to withstand the rigors of the game.(n)

programme.title: Inazuma Eleven Go: Arion, the New Captain
programme.desc: The match against Universal is over, and Riccardo, who fell during the game, is undergoing emergency surgery. This puts the team captain out for the upcoming Holy Road championship, a major blow to Raimon's hopes.(n)

programme.title: Inazuma Eleven Go: Showdown in Zenith Stadium

programme.title: Space: The New Frontier: Sling Shot

programme.title: Space: The New Frontier: Living Planet

programme.title: Space: The New Frontier: Cosmic Collisions

programme.title: Space: The New Frontier: Gravity
programme.desc: Gravity keeps us on the ground and the planets in their orbits, yet we only notice it when it's not there. In space we cheat gravity; falling just as fast but missing the ground. Now this fundamental universal force is slowly giving up its secrets.(n)

programme.title: Space: The New Frontier: Interface
programme.desc: The interface between Earth and space is the Ionosphere, a region of rarified gas and charged particles. It is very important for radio communications, radar, satellite signals and global positioning. Yet we know so little about it.(n)

programme.title: Space: The New Frontier: From There to Here

programme.title: The Embassy: Episode 2
programme.desc: The embassy is called to a young couple in crisis. Their 7 month-old baby girl, Laney, has died from a virus and they need to get her home to Australia. But can they get baby Laney on the plane?(n)

programme.title: The Embassy: Episode 3
programme.desc: The embassy is on high alert after a wealthy Australian banker goes missing. Is he alive? Holed up in a bar somewhere? Or does he not want to be found?(n)

programme.title: The Embassy: Episode 4

programme.title: The Embassy: Episode 5

programme.title: The Embassy: Episode 6

programme.title: The Embassy: Episode 7

programme.title: Classic: BMW
programme.desc: The BMW 319 was introduced as a sports car in 1934 with the new 1.9-litre six-cylinder engine - as the successor to the 315/1 Sport, from which it hardly differed externally.

programme.title: Classic: Bugatti / Chevrolet Corvair / Chrysler Airflow
programme.desc: In 1935, the racing driver Gaston Descollas won the most important French long-distance race, the Paris-Nice Rally, in a Bugatti Type 57. Now a German Bugatti specialist sits behind the wheel of this car, as he once did.

programme.title: Classic: Citroën 2CV / Concorso d'Eleganza am Comer See / Studebaker Avanti
programme.desc: In the mid-1930s, Pierre Boulanger, the general manager of Citroën, had the idea of developing a small, practical car tailored to the rural population. At the end of 1937, the development of the world-famous 2CV began.

programme.title: Classic: F12 Roadster / Lamborghini
programme.desc: More than 50 years ago, the engineers of the Ingolstadt car manufacturer DKW presented the F 12 Roadster, the last passenger car of the traditional brand.

programme.title: Classic: Jaguar / Fiat
programme.desc: On 15 March 1961, the Jaguar E-Type Coupé was presented to the public at the Geneva Motor Show. The reactions to the extraordinary Jaguar were predominantly positive. In Geneva alone, 500 E-Types were pre-ordered.(n)

programme.title: Classic: Toyota / Renault
programme.desc: The Toyota Land Cruiser is more successful than the off-road vehicles from Mercedes, Land Rover and Co. The Land Cruiser's ease of spare parts procurement makes all the difference. This bush taxi really gets everything and everyone from A to B.(n)

programme.title: Classic: Audi / Der Beradino / Facel Vega Facellia
programme.desc: Audi revolutionised the rally world with the Quattro. We present the rally history of the Audi Quattro from its beginnings in 1980 to its successes in Group B and its victory at Pikes Peak.(n)

programme.title: Classic: Porsche
programme.desc: The Porsche Type 64, of which only three were built, is based on the Volkswagen and produces 35 hp. Due to its aerodynamic shape, the top speed is 160 km/h.(n)

programme.title: Classic: Käfer / Ente / Glas
programme.desc: A Volkswagen Beetle with a 1970s look and contemporary tuning. 90 hp and 180 km/h top speed promise endless driving fun.(n)

programme.title: Classic: Josef Stalins ZIS 110 / Melkus RS 1000 / Opel Kapitän 'Kapinator'
programme.desc: James Bond does not yet have a licence to kill when this Russian limousine called ZIS-110 rolls off the production line in 1949. In the 1940s and 50s, this pirated Packard became a popular means of transport for Soviet political celebrities.(n)

programme.title: Classic: Mercedes / Wanderer Stromlinie Spezial
programme.desc: We had the chance to test one of only 29 built Mercedes 300 SL 'Lightweight' on its premiere run at the Mille Miglia.(n)

programme.title: Classic: Classic Car with Blue Lights / Rolls-Royce Silver Wraith / Skoda 110 R
programme.desc: Until the reunification of Germany in 1989, Berlin was politically, economically and culturally divided into East and West and accordingly had two police forces. In front of and behind the wall, the officers used different vehicles.(n)

programme.title: Classic Races: Pikes Peak
programme.desc: The Pikes Peak Hill Climb is a rather different type of race in the mountains of Colorado, USA. It's unique, fascinating and full of adventure. One of the starters at the 1987 Pikes Peak is two-time rally world champion Walter Röhrl.(n)

programme.title: Classic Races: Grand Prix Races since 1934
programme.desc: Since 1934 the Grand Prix has been the most exciting and fascinating world championship in the world. With its state-of-the-art vehicles featuring horsepower from the biggest brands, it never fails to wow its viewers.(n)

programme.title: Classic Races: Rallye Year 1972 - A Ford Success Story
programme.desc: The international championship for manufacturers was a rally series which ran from 1970 to 1972. Car manufacturers such as Porsche, Renault and Ford all took part, with Ford having an exceptionally successful year in 1972.(n)

programme.title: Classic Races: German Touring Championship 1992
programme.desc: The 1992 German Touring Car Championship is one of the most important racing series in German motorsport for sure. It's hard, merciless and well known for its die-hard battles between the ruthless competitors.(n)

programme.title: Classic Races: Touring Car Grand Prix, Argentina 1964
programme.desc: Tropical temperatures, never-ending dust and curves: those are just some of the many difficulties for man and machine during the 1964 Grand Prix in Argentina. This race was responsible for taking the Mercedes brand to the top.(n)

programme.title: Classic Races: Indy 500 1994
programme.desc: The Indy 500 is one of the world's most spectacular motor races in the world. Watched by a huge number of people, this motorsports event doesn't fail to impress at the Indianapolis Motor Speedway.(n)

programme.title: Classic Races: German Rallye Championship 1983
programme.desc: The German rally championship is one of the most popular motorsport series and has been running since 1970. At the 1983 race, the sporty models from Opel saw exceptional success.(n)

programme.title: Classic Races: Quattro The New Dimension 1985
programme.desc: With the introduction of the Group D-Monsters in the World Rally Championships, the fight for the title got harder and harder. Thats why Audi brought a strong trump onto the road in 1985 - The Sport Quattro. And with it began a new dimension.(n)

programme.title: Classic Races: The Rallye World Championship 1982
programme.desc: The African continent is always a difficult terrain for rally drivers. That wasn't any different for the 1982 World Rally Championship, when heat, dust, mud and hardly passable routes posed major challenges for drivers, co-drivers and engines.(n)

programme.title: Classic Races: Mercedes Races Again 1954/55
programme.desc: In 1954, after more than 20 years of abstinence, Mercedes returns to Grand Prix racing. With a lot of engagement, advanced engineering and with the best Grand-Prix-drivers of the world, Mercedes wanted to enjoy success in motorsports again.(n)

programme.title: Classic Ride: Amphicar
programme.desc: The Amphicar 770 is a rare classic. Its special attraction is that you drive motorboat on the road. It may not be the fastest car on the street, but it’s ready to be used on the water as well.(n)

programme.title: Classic Ride: MG TC
programme.desc: The MG TC is a sporty, but also extremely spartan car with technology from the late 1940s. Thus the car might be somewhat susceptible to technical problems, but it’s very easy to maintain.(n)

programme.title: Classic Ride: BMW 319
programme.desc: The BMW 319/1 is one of the rarest and most demanded pre-war classic cars from Germany. Only 178 of them were ever built. Nowadays a well-maintained BMW 319/1 costs more than a Ferrari.(n)

programme.title: Classic Ride: Ron William's Cadillac
programme.desc: The 1952 Cadillac Fleetwood is also known as the American Rolls-Royce, because it’s the car of celebrities, presidents, millionaires and mafia bosses. Only around 16,000 units were built, so it’s a treasured collector’s piece.(n)

programme.title: Classic Ride: Jaguar E-Type
programme.desc: A legend celebrates its 50th anniversary. In 1961 The Jaguar E-Type was shown for the first time on the Motor Show Geneva.(n)

programme.title: Sanctuary: Out Of The Blue
programme.desc: Meet Helen and Will: neighbors on a tree-lined, suburban street. Helen lives alone, dislikes her neighbor’s dog and is a talented painter.

programme.title: Sanctuary: Into The Black
programme.desc: The Sanctuary receives alarming news that a large group of Abnormals has been spotted at the entrance to a cave in South Dakota.

programme.title: Sanctuary: Tempus
programme.desc: Adam Worth destroys Praxis and travels back in time to the 1890s to save his daughter. Dr. Magnus travels back in time to stop him before he damages the time line and destroys her future with it.

programme.title: Sanctuary: Uprising
programme.desc: With Magnus gone, Will is appointed the head of the Sanctuary Network. The abnormal uprising continues to get worse. Biggie and Kate are kidnapped. As expected the surface governments respond to the uprising with deadly force.(n)

programme.title: Sanctuary
programme.desc: The UN Security Council sends a task force headed by a weasel of a man, Greg Addison, to investigate the Sanctuary. His disdain for abnormals is matched by the disdain that Magnus and team have for him.(n)

programme.title: Sanctuary
programme.desc: Since the UN no longer backs the Sanctuary, Magnus makes other arrangements for her finances. A planned meeting in Africa with a potential banker turns into a hostage situation. Will and Henry search for an abnormal in the Old City tunnels.(n)

programme.title: Sanctuary: Resistance
programme.desc: Helen and Henry break into a government abnormal research facility called SCIU - only to find it is run by Tesla. Biggie and Will deal with an annoying abnormal named Galvo.(n)

programme.title: Sanctuary: Homecoming
programme.desc: Will's trip to Liberia turns bad when he suffers a head trauma from an attack. The trauma brings up powerful memories about his mothers death and the inadequacies of his father. Magnus deals with be-winged scam artist.(n)

programme.title: Degrassi: The Next Generation: Secrets & Lies
programme.desc: After a long absence overseas, Ashley's dad is back in town. She's enjoying his company and attention, but something tells her there's a piece of his life that's being kept from her.(n)

programme.title: Earth: Final Conflict: Apparition
programme.desc: Liam investigates the suspicious death of a banker, which he saw in a dream. It seems to be an exiled Taelon spirit that is contacting him. Da'an berates Zo'or for his money and power hungry attitude.(n)

programme.title: Earth: Final Conflict: One Taelon Avenue
programme.desc: Joshua Doors is running his own technology development company and Renee goes undercover to find out what is going on. An artificial intelligence program of the Taelons that controls human minds seems to be acting on its own.(n)

programme.title: Earth: Final Conflict: Abduction
programme.desc: A volunteer who was working to interpret an ancient message from Ma'el assaults Da'an and escapes through a portal. Sandoval helps Da'an avoid interrogation from Zo'or while they try to locate her.(n)

programme.title: Earth: Final Conflict: Arrival
programme.desc: A Taelon shuttle is shot down over Antarctica. There are Jiridians aboard, but two of the passengers escape. When Augur discovers Lili's blood on the ship, he is convinced that she is not dead.(n)

programme.title: Earth: Final Conflict: The Forge of Creation
programme.desc: Lili, Vorjak, and the baby flee to find a shuttle to escape Earth. Liam and Sandoval are both tracking them - for different reasons. Augur is on the run from volunteers, but sends a friend (Juliet) to help Liam while he's gone.(n)

programme.title: Earth: Final Conflict: First Breath
programme.desc: A college friend of Renee's resurfaces and leads them on an investigation of the link between the Taelons and a biomedical facility's cloning operation.(n)

programme.title: Earth: Final Conflict: Sins of the Father
programme.desc: A Senator's daughter is found to have kryss in her system. Liam and Renee suspect the Taelons lied about synthesizing it and there is a new location for production. They believe Federov is involved. Da'an is addicted to kryss.(n)

programme.title: Earth: Final Conflict: Limbo
programme.desc: The Taelons lend some of their dwindling core energy to Joshua Doors for a pilot cold fusion project, but the energy is stolen, leaving the Taelons vulnerable. Jonathan Doors lives on as an AI in cyberspace.(n)
